com.bluegosling.collections

Interface CanonicalSet<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements in the set
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, Set<E>

    public interface CanonicalSet<E>
extends Set<E>
    A set that can also provide the canonical instance for a given value.

      • newCanonicalSetFromMap

        static <E> CanonicalSet<E> newCanonicalSetFromMap(Map<E,E> map)
        Creates a new canonical set backed by the given map. The map should not be used to store arbitrary mappings as it is expected that a value is always equal to its corresponding key. As items are added to this canonical set, that is how mappings are added to the backing map. The values in the map are also used to canonicalize the contents of the set.
        Parameters:
        map - a map
        Returns:
        a canonical set backed by the given map
